Hi
This is a reminder document for Heroku CLI commands

* First you need to download the heroku CLI from the website according to your OS.

COMMANDS
*********

heroku --version            --  check if you have heroku cli in your cmd.
heroku login                --  connect to heroku server for changes.
heroku ps -a APPNAME        --  gives dyno info - how many hours left/used.
heroku ps:scale -a APPNAME  --  gives which dynos are availble for the app and their status. ( dyno = resources, for example, web dyno = http requests).
heroku info -a APPNAME      --  gives APP info.
heroku maintenance -a APPNAME -- gives maintenance status.
heroku maintenance:on/off -a APPNAME -- turn maintenance on/off.
heroku ps:scale DYNONAME =0 -a APPNAME -- turn specific dyno on/off.

